The Poisson App

Iga Korneta
August 11, 2014

Ever felt the need to see the Poisson distribution?

Like, if you needed to do Statistical Inference Project 1?

Poisson distribution:

  • \( \lambda^x e^{-\lambda}/x! \)
  • depends on \( \lambda \)
  • n (number of samples) also nice

Poisson App:

  • takes in n, \( \lambda \)
  • draws n samples
  • draws histogram of samples (ggplot2)
  • also shows summary, table of counts
x <- data.frame (samples=rpois(n, lambda))

p <- ggplot(x, aes(x=samples))

p <- p + geom_bar(fill="light green")

p <-  p + theme_bw() + xlab("Random samples") + ylab("Count")

p
